              <h3>National Review of Asthma Deaths (NRAD) one year on: Improving Asthma diagnosis and reducing hospital admissions</h3>
              <p>8<sup>th</sup> July 2015 at 12.30-13.15</p>
              <p>Join Dr Mark Levy, the NRAD Clinical Lead, as he presents his thoughts on the 2014 National Report of Asthma Deaths one year after its publication, and what can be learnt from it. He will examine the next steps, the importance of treating Asthma as a chronic disease, and the need for ongoing assessment and control. Dan Murphy from Asthma UK will be co-presenting the meeting and will share the patient perspective of NRAD one year on.</p>
